result.name: Natural Sciences B.S. - Science Education Option

templateAssets.content:
• The option in science education is designed for students preparing to be middle school science teachers, or seeking a career as an informal science educator in a museum or outdoor setting such as state parks, environmental camps, or nature centers.
  • Successful completion of the program fulfills one of the requirements for admission into a single subject teaching credential program.

In sections below where the student is directed to select courses and there is a note "Only lower division courses listed," upper division courses are also available. See the University Catalog for the full listing of degree requirements.
